  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Investigators compare the accuracy of the SpHb and hemocue with blood Hb levels
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The goal of the study is to compare 3 methods of hemoglobin measurement in pediatric patients
      undergoing major surgery. During general anesthesia investigators will measure and compare at
      different periods of time blood hemoglobin levels obtained from a radial artery catheter with
      2 non invasive methods of measurement using hemocue and SpHb
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
